                              <td width="100%" class="TableCell">
                                 <h2>Journal 01. My humble beginnings...</h2>
                              </td>
                           </tr>
                           <tr>
                              <td width="100%" class="TableCell"><i>Well, when and where I came from may be a good way to start this whole journal, though my start is as shifty as my being....</i></td>
                           </tr>
                        </table>
                        <table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
                           <tr>
                              <td width="100%" class="TableCellHeading"><b><i>Campaign Entry of The beginning...</i></b></td>
                           </tr>
                           <tr>
                              <td width="100%" class="TableCellAlternate">
                                 Number of times read: 202,
                                 Entry created on 27 July 2004 06:54,
                                 Last updated on 27 July 2004 06:54
                                 <p></p>
                                 
                                 In the campaign at time of entry:
                                 <br><ul>
                                    <li><b>N'riahn the Stout</b> - Human Elementalist
                                    </li>
                                 </ul>
                              </td>
                           </tr>
                           <tr>
                              <td width="100%" class="TableCell"><b>From the bland city of Blaan to the Shores of FIre...</b><br>
                                 As written by N'riahn the Stout on 27 July 2004 06:54
                                 <p></p>Somewhere between the Jerris and the Mist Swamps, as vague a geographical location as it may be, is the unexciting village
                                 of Blaan.  Sporting all manner of goods and services and being located right on a major trade route, though a promising start,
                                 did not mean people would stay in Blaan.  Only when forced to stay by heavy rains did trade caravans stay in town, and took
                                 advantage of the local Smithy, the Tavern, and the Brothel.
                                 <p></p>It was on such a night that I was conceived.
                                 <p></p>That's right:  My mother was a prostitute, and my father was a traveller I will never meet.  Perhaps the rains that forced
                                 my conception we're an omen from the Elements, along with my persistent meddling with puddles of mud, the nearby Mists, and
                                 other local natural phenomenon.
                                 <p></p>Regardless, I was discovered by a travelling dwarf who tackled the way of the Elementalist, and took me to the Death's Sea
                                 where my training would commence.  My only loss was Nana, a local widow in Blaan who took the job of raising me while my mother
                                 continued her nocturnal exploits.
                                 <p></p>Her parting gift to me, a yellow, silken scarf, would become my grimoire.<br></td>
                           </tr>
                        </table>
