                           <tr>
                              <td width="100%" class="TableCell"><b>Enough with Fire!</b><br>
                                 As written by N'riahn the Stout on 27 July 2004 06:56
                                 <p></p>My training at the Sea took place during an arduous 6 months, where many lessons were quickly learned.  I had mastered a few
                                 spells and was a welcome addition to the several crews that went Fire Elemental mining.
                                 <p></p>Though too inexperienced to actually assist in Fire Gathering, I would help the crew where I could with Air Armour, Resist
                                 Fire, Heal Food, and other spells being cast when required.  It was also interesting to hear the first-hand account of near-death
                                 experiences, wonderous sights, and tales of the province I will evenutally discover for myself.
                                 <p></p>There was one point of tension during all this majesty: my teacher.  The dwarf, who shall remain nameless, is a Specialist
                                 Elementalist who's focus was mainly on the Element of Fire.  Though no animosity existed, I felt pressured to pursue the same
                                 path, and felt leaving the Sea would be the best way for me to know what my path trully is; after all, Fire was the only Element
                                 I knew.
                                 <p></p>Though hesitant, my teacher understood the honesty of my words and sent me to the Twilight Peaks where his friendship with
                                 the Stonetooth Clan would buy me passage with the Trolls.  There I would be exposed to the gracefulness and might of Air and
                                 Earth.
                                 <p></p>After a week's journey, I arrived...<br></td>
